We start by extracting the required numbers from the provided three statements.

1. Current Ratio  
   Definition: Current Assets ÷ Current Liabilities  
   • Total Current Assets = 9,891,156.92  
   • Total Current Liabilities = 631,880.98  
   Calculation: 9,891,156.92 ÷ 631,880.98 ≈ 15.65

2. Gross Profit Margin  
   Definition: (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100%  
   • Gross Profit = 2,060,619.40  
   • Total Revenue = 3,397,619.40  
   Calculation: 2,060,619.40 ÷ 3,397,619.40 ≈ 0.6063 = 60.63%

3. Debt to Asset Ratio  
   Definition: Total Liabilities ÷ Total Assets  
   • Total Liabilities (only current liabilities are provided) = 631,880.98  
   • Total Assets = 14,799,664.61  
   Calculation: 631,880.98 ÷ 14,799,664.61 ≈ 0.0427, which rounds to 0.04

4. Net Profit Margin  
   Definition: (Net Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100%  
   • Net Profit = 1,167,783.63  
   • Total Revenue = 3,397,619.40  
   Calculation: 1,167,783.63 ÷ 3,397,619.40 ≈ 0.3437 = 34.37%

5. Cash to Current Debt Ratio  
   Definition: Cash and Cash Equivalents ÷ Current Liabilities  
   • Cash on Hand = 2,339,224.10  
   • Bank Deposits = 4,292,000.00  
   • Cash and Cash Equivalents = 2,339,224.10 + 4,292,000.00 = 6,631,224.10  
   • Current Liabilities = 631,880.98  
   Calculation: 6,631,224.10 ÷ 631,880.98 ≈ 10.50

6. Free Cash Flow (FCF)  
   Definition: FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities – Capital Expenditures  
   • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –1,368,775.90  
   • Purchase of Fixed Assets = –0.00  
   Calculation: –1,368,775.90 – 0 = –1,368,775.90

7. Return on Assets (ROA)  
   Definition: (Net Profit ÷ Total Assets) × 100%  
   • Net Profit = 1,167,783.63  
   • Total Assets = 14,799,664.61  
   Calculation: 1,167,783.63 ÷ 14,799,664.61 ≈ 0.0789 = 7.90%
